#
# how to install corpora, yaml and bsddb in python
#
1) prerequisites: yaml, bsddb,
    pip install -U pyyaml
    brew install berkeley-db4
    sudo BERKELEYDB_DIR='`brew --prefix`/opt/berkeley-db@4' pip install -U bsddb3
    
2) pip install corpora

3) in python CLI,
  >>> import corpora
  
4) once 'pip install bsddb3' fails, try:
    Method 1. brew install berkeley-db4
              sudo BERKELEYDB_DIR='`brew --prefix`/opt/berkeley-db@4' pip install -U bsddb3
              
    Method 2. install anaconda
              install bsddb via conda install
              
   # ref:   ImportError: No module named _bsddb https://stackoverflow.com/questions/44829520/importerror-no-module-named-bsddb
   # ref:   Installing bsddb package - python   https://stackoverflow.com/questions/16003224/installing-bsddb-package-python
   
   
# ref:  ImportError: No Module named yaml | Ansible https://stackoverflow.com/questions/38131804/importerror-no-module-named-yaml-ansible


